My Education Journey

1990-2005

Early Education in Kalamata, Greece

Primary and Secondary School Education. Developed an early interest in math, science, and technology.

2005-2009

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science

University of Kalamata, Greece. Focused on programming, algorithms, and the fundamentals of robotics and control systems.

2010-2012

Summer Internships in Robotics

Interned at robotics companies and research institutions. Gained hands-on experience in motion planning and control systems.

2012-2015

Master’s Degree in Robotics

ETH Zurich, Switzerland. Specialized in motion planning, dynamical systems, and reinforcement learning.

2015-Present

Robotics Software Engineer

Currently working as a robotics software engineer. Passionate about developing algorithms for motion planning and reinforcement learning.

Ongoing

Continued Professional Development

Attending conferences, publishing research papers, and collaborating with international experts in robotics.
